42 setup tile buffer
43
44
45 Arduino Uno Text Example
46> FONT_ROTATION INTERSECTION CLIPPING text data bss dec hex
47> 8700
48> x x x 7450 104 1116 8670 21de
49> - x x 7132 104 1115 8351 209f
50> x - x 7230 104 1116 8450 2102
51> - - x 7010 104 1115 8229 2025
52> - - - 6880 104 1115 8099 1fa3

62/*
63 The following macro enables 16 Bit mode.
64 Without defining this macro all calulations are done with 8 Bit (1 Byte) variables.
65 Especially on AVR architecture, this will save some space.
66 If this macro is defined, then U8g2 will switch to 16 Bit mode.
67 Use 16 Bit mode for any display with more than 240 pixel in one
68 direction.
69*/
70//#define U8G2_16BIT
71
72/*
73 The following macro switches the library into dynamic display buffer allocation mode.
74 Defining this constant will disable all static memory allocation for device memory buffer and thus allows the user to allocate device buffers statically.
75 Before using any display functions, the dynamic buffer *must* be assigned to the u8g2 struct using the u8g2_SetBufferPtr function.
76 When using dynamic allocation, the stack size must be increased by u8g2_GetBufferSize bytes.
77 */
78//#define U8G2_USE_DYNAMIC_ALLOC
79
80/* U8g2 feature selection, see also https://github.com/olikraus/u8g2/wiki/u8g2optimization */
81
82/*
83 The following macro enables the HVLine speed optimization.
84 It will consume about 40 bytes more in flash memory of the AVR.
85 HVLine procedures are also used by the text drawing functions.
86*/
87#define U8G2_WITH_HVLINE_SPEED_OPTIMIZATION
88
89/*
90 The following macro activates the early intersection check with the current visible area.
91 Clipping (and low level intersection calculation) will still happen and is controlled by U8G2_WITH_CLIPPING.
92 This early intersection check only improves speed for the picture loop (u8g2_FirstPage/NextPage).
93 With a full framebuffer in RAM and if most graphical elements are drawn within the visible area, then this
94 macro can be commented to reduce code size.
95*/
96#define U8G2_WITH_INTERSECTION
97
98/*
99 Enable clip window support:
100 void u8g2_SetMaxClipWindow(u8g2_t *u8g2)
101 void u8g2_SetClipWindow(u8g2_t *u8g2, u8g2_uint_t clip_x0, u8g2_uint_t clip_y0, u8g2_uint_t clip_x1, u8g2_uint_t clip_y1 )
102 Setting a clip window will restrict all drawing to this window.
103 Clip window support requires about 200 bytes flash memory on AVR systems
104*/
105#define U8G2_WITH_CLIP_WINDOW_SUPPORT
106
107/*
108 The following macro enables all four drawing directions for glyphs and strings.
109 If this macro is not defined, than a string can be drawn only in horizontal direction.
110
111 Jan 2020: Disabling this macro will save up to 600 bytes on AVR
112*/
113#define U8G2_WITH_FONT_ROTATION
114
115/*
116 U8glib V2 contains support for unicode plane 0 (Basic Multilingual Plane, BMP).
117 The following macro activates this support. Deactivation would save some ROM.
118 This definition also defines the behavior of the expected string encoding.
119 If the following macro is defined, then the DrawUTF8 function is enabled and
120 the string argument for this function is assumed
121 to be UTF-8 encoded.
122 If the following macro is not defined, then all strings in the c-code are assumed
123 to be ISO 8859-1/CP1252 encoded.
124 Independently from this macro, the Arduino print function never accepts UTF-8
125 strings.
126
127 This macro does not affect the u8x8 string draw function.
128 u8x8 has also two function, one for pure strings and one for UTF8
129
130 Conclusion:
131 U8G2_WITH_UNICODE defined
132 - C-Code Strings must be UTF-8 encoded
133 - Full support of all 65536 glyphs of the unicode basic multilingual plane
134 - Up to 65536 glyphs of the font file can be used.
135 U8G2_WITH_UNICODE not defined
136 - C-Code Strings are assumbed to be ISO 8859-1/CP1252 encoded
137 - Only character values 0 to 255 are supported in the font file.
138*/
139#define U8G2_WITH_UNICODE
140

169#ifdef U8G2_16BIT
170typedef uint16_t u8g2_uint_t; /* for pixel position only */
171typedef int16_t u8g2_int_t; /* introduced for circle calculation */
172typedef int32_t u8g2_long_t; /* introduced for ellipse calculation */
173#else
174typedef uint8_t u8g2_uint_t; /* for pixel position only */
175typedef int8_t u8g2_int_t; /* introduced for circle calculation */
176typedef int16_t u8g2_long_t; /* introduced for ellipse calculation */
177#endif
178
179typedef struct u8g2_struct u8g2_t;
180typedef struct u8g2_cb_struct u8g2_cb_t;
181
182typedef void (*u8g2_update_dimension_cb)(u8g2_t* u8g2);
183typedef void (*u8g2_update_page_win_cb)(u8g2_t* u8g2);
184typedef void (
185 *u8g2_draw_l90_cb)(u8g2_t* u8g2, u8g2_uint_t x, u8g2_uint_t y, u8g2_uint_t len, uint8_t dir);
186typedef void (*u8g2_draw_ll_hvline_cb)(
187 u8g2_t* u8g2,
188 u8g2_uint_t x,
189 u8g2_uint_t y,
190 u8g2_uint_t len,
191 uint8_t dir);
192
193typedef uint8_t (*u8g2_get_kerning_cb)(u8g2_t* u8g2, uint16_t e1, uint16_t e2);

195/* from ucglib... */
196struct _u8g2_font_info_t {
197 /* offset 0 */
198 uint8_t glyph_cnt;
199 uint8_t bbx_mode;
200 uint8_t bits_per_0;
201 uint8_t bits_per_1;
202
203 /* offset 4 */
204 uint8_t bits_per_char_width;
205 uint8_t bits_per_char_height;
206 uint8_t bits_per_char_x;
207 uint8_t bits_per_char_y;
208 uint8_t bits_per_delta_x;
209
210 /* offset 9 */
211 int8_t max_char_width;
212 int8_t
213 max_char_height; /* overall height, NOT ascent. Instead ascent = max_char_height + y_offset */
214 int8_t x_offset;
215 int8_t y_offset;
216
217 /* offset 13 */
218 int8_t ascent_A;
219 int8_t descent_g; /* usually a negative value */
220 int8_t ascent_para;
221 int8_t descent_para;
222
223 /* offset 17 */
224 uint16_t start_pos_upper_A;
225 uint16_t start_pos_lower_a;
226
227 /* offset 21 */
228#ifdef U8G2_WITH_UNICODE
229 uint16_t start_pos_unicode;
230#endif
231};
232typedef struct _u8g2_font_info_t u8g2_font_info_t;
233
234/* from ucglib... */
235struct _u8g2_font_decode_t {
236 const uint8_t* decode_ptr; /* pointer to the compressed data */
237
238 u8g2_uint_t target_x;
239 u8g2_uint_t target_y;
240
241 int8_t x; /* local coordinates, (0,0) is upper left */
242 int8_t y;
243 int8_t glyph_width;
244 int8_t glyph_height;
245
246 uint8_t decode_bit_pos; /* bitpos inside a byte of the compressed data */
247 uint8_t is_transparent;
248 uint8_t fg_color;
249 uint8_t bg_color;
250#ifdef U8G2_WITH_FONT_ROTATION
251 uint8_t dir; /* direction */
252#endif
253};
254typedef struct _u8g2_font_decode_t u8g2_font_decode_t;
255
256struct _u8g2_kerning_t {
257 uint16_t first_table_cnt;
258 uint16_t second_table_cnt;
259 const uint16_t* first_encoding_table;
260 const uint16_t* index_to_second_table;
261 const uint16_t* second_encoding_table;
262 const uint8_t* kerning_values;
263};
264typedef struct _u8g2_kerning_t u8g2_kerning_t;
265
266struct u8g2_cb_struct {
267 u8g2_update_dimension_cb update_dimension;
268 u8g2_update_page_win_cb update_page_win;
269 u8g2_draw_l90_cb draw_l90;
270};
271
272typedef u8g2_uint_t (*u8g2_font_calc_vref_fnptr)(u8g2_t* u8g2);
273
274struct u8g2_struct {
275 u8x8_t u8x8;
276 u8g2_draw_ll_hvline_cb ll_hvline; /* low level hvline procedure */
277 const u8g2_cb_t* cb; /* callback drawprocedures, can be replaced for rotation */
278
279 /* the following variables must be assigned during u8g2 setup */
280 uint8_t*
281 tile_buf_ptr; /* ptr to memory area with u8x8.display_info->tile_width * 8 * tile_buf_height bytes */
282 uint8_t tile_buf_height; /* height of the tile memory area in tile rows */
283 uint8_t tile_curr_row; /* current row for picture loop */
284
285 /* dimension of the buffer in pixel */
286 u8g2_uint_t pixel_buf_width; /* equal to tile_buf_width*8 */
287 u8g2_uint_t pixel_buf_height; /* tile_buf_height*8 */
288 u8g2_uint_t pixel_curr_row; /* u8g2.tile_curr_row*8 */
289
290 /* the following variables are set by the update dimension callback */
291 /* this is the clipbox after rotation for the hvline procedures */
292 //u8g2_uint_t buf_x0; /* left corner of the buffer */
293 //u8g2_uint_t buf_x1; /* right corner of the buffer (excluded) */
294 u8g2_uint_t buf_y0;
295 u8g2_uint_t buf_y1;
296
297 /* display dimensions in pixel for the user, calculated in u8g2_update_dimension_common() */
298 u8g2_uint_t width;
299 u8g2_uint_t height;
300
301 /* ths is the clip box for the user to check if a specific box has an intersection */
302 /* use u8g2_IsIntersection from u8g2_intersection.c to test against this intersection */
303 /* actually, this window describes the positon of the current page */
304 u8g2_uint_t user_x0; /* left corner of the buffer */
305 u8g2_uint_t user_x1; /* right corner of the buffer (excluded) */
306 u8g2_uint_t user_y0; /* upper edge of the buffer */
307 u8g2_uint_t user_y1; /* lower edge of the buffer (excluded) */
308
309#ifdef U8G2_WITH_CLIP_WINDOW_SUPPORT
310 /* clip window */
311 u8g2_uint_t clip_x0; /* left corner of the clip window */
312 u8g2_uint_t clip_x1; /* right corner of the clip window (excluded) */
313 u8g2_uint_t clip_y0; /* upper edge of the clip window */
314 u8g2_uint_t clip_y1; /* lower edge of the clip window (excluded) */
315#endif /* U8G2_WITH_CLIP_WINDOW_SUPPORT */
316
317 /* information about the current font */
318 const uint8_t* font; /* current font for all text procedures */
319 // removed: const u8g2_kerning_t *kerning; /* can be NULL */
320 // removed: u8g2_get_kerning_cb get_kerning_cb;
321
322 u8g2_font_calc_vref_fnptr font_calc_vref;
323 u8g2_font_decode_t font_decode; /* new font decode structure */
324 u8g2_font_info_t font_info; /* new font info structure */
325
326#ifdef U8G2_WITH_CLIP_WINDOW_SUPPORT
327 /* 1 of there is an intersection between user_?? and clip_?? box */
328 uint8_t is_page_clip_window_intersection;
329#endif /* U8G2_WITH_CLIP_WINDOW_SUPPORT */
330
331 uint8_t font_height_mode;
332 int8_t font_ref_ascent;
333 int8_t font_ref_descent;
334
335 int8_t glyph_x_offset; /* set by u8g2_GetGlyphWidth as a side effect */
336
337 uint8_t bitmap_transparency; /* black pixels will be treated as transparent (not drawn) */
338
339 uint8_t draw_color; /* 0: clear pixel, 1: set pixel, modified and restored by font procedures */
340 /* draw_color can be used also directly by the user API */
341
342 // the following variable should be renamed to is_buffer_auto_clear
343 uint8_t
344 is_auto_page_clear; /* set to 0 to disable automatic clear of the buffer in firstPage() and nextPage() */
345};
